And I broughtyou your new fans.

594
00:44:57,458 --> 00:45:01,394
Jimmy, Lorenzo, Covonne.
Guys. Trese.

595
00:45:01,395 --> 00:45:03,361
- Vivian.
- Vivian.

596
00:45:03,362 --> 00:45:05,549
Hi guys. Thank
you for coming.

597
00:45:05,550 --> 00:45:07,666
Los muchachos on
your old block

598
00:45:07,667 --> 00:45:10,603
were probably itchin' for
your quinceañera.

599
00:45:10,604 --> 00:45:15,604
They probably could not
wait for you to come of age.

600
00:45:15,909 --> 00:45:17,911
Excuse me.
Do you have a pen?

601
00:45:17,912 --> 00:45:19,845
Is that your friend?
- No.

602
00:45:19,846 --> 00:45:23,017
- I'm friends with those two.
- I'm on stage next.

603
00:45:23,018 --> 00:45:25,185
So I'll see
you guys later.

604
00:45:25,186 --> 00:45:28,376
- Good luck!
- Adios!

605
00:45:40,468 --> 00:45:46,374
You don't look like you feel well.
Shouldn't you be in bed or something?

606
00:45:46,375 --> 00:45:50,478
I've seen every one of Trese's
performances this year.

607
00:45:50,479 --> 00:45:53,715
That's 36 more than
you've been to, bub.

608
00:45:53,716 --> 00:45:57,475
And I'm not about
to miss this one.

609
00:45:59,553 --> 00:46:04,156
- You're a real classy lady.
- You're buying.

610
00:46:12,134 --> 00:46:17,362
This was inspired by
the man at that table.

611
00:46:18,874 --> 00:46:20,563
His name is Jimmy.

612
00:46:22,310 --> 00:46:26,468
What? Yeah, because
I got it like that!

613
00:46:30,820 --> 00:46:36,491
Having curly hair and yellow skin does not
mean that I don't know my black father.

614
00:46:36,492 --> 00:46:39,799
And just because
I have to get a tan...

615
00:46:39,800 --> 00:46:43,433
doesn't mean that I am
confused about my identity.

616
00:46:43,434 --> 00:46:50,505
So no you are not too "black"
for me. You are just ugly.

617
00:46:50,506 --> 00:46:55,178
And being darker than me doesn't give you
the right to identify my proper identity

618
00:46:55,179 --> 00:46:59,817
just because you are uncomfortable
being more negro que la negra.

619
00:46:59,818 --> 00:47:03,086
In the city, I am
suddenly Puertoriquena

620
00:47:03,087 --> 00:47:08,426
as beautiful men with
beautiful voices ask me

621
00:47:08,427 --> 00:47:12,898
Eres Boriqua? Brazilena?
Dominicana? Cubana?

622
00:47:12,899 --> 00:47:17,300
So I am sorry if what
you see confuses you.

623
00:47:17,301 --> 00:47:19,936
If you do not know how to
put me in the file folder

624
00:47:19,937 --> 00:47:24,475
that can be easily shelved in the
census bureau of your brain.

625
00:47:24,476 --> 00:47:27,010
I will not placate you.

626
00:47:27,011 --> 00:47:30,932
So include me when you mention
those 7 black people you know.

627
00:47:30,933 --> 00:47:34,785
Because I am not different on
account of you feeling I look so.

628
00:47:34,786 --> 00:47:41,660
Me, an item of mystification, not to be
confused by your bureaucracy of thought.

629
00:47:41,661 --> 00:47:43,527
I am something
higher than race

630
00:47:43,528 --> 00:47:47,231
bigger than the color strands of your
hair or the tint in your skin.

631
00:47:47,232 --> 00:47:52,040
I am not multicultural.
I am universal.

632
00:47:52,341 --> 00:47:57,241
And that has nothing to do
with race.

633
00:48:01,147 --> 00:48:03,906
So let's scramble.

634
00:48:11,390 --> 00:48:14,615
So why are you
really here?

635
00:48:16,262 --> 00:48:19,233
You know when you question
everything I do, it makes you...

636
00:48:19,234 --> 00:48:21,700
...you're at your
least attractive.

637
00:48:21,701 --> 00:48:25,302
So there are times when
you find me attractive?

638
00:48:29,843 --> 00:48:34,026
Well, you did show up
with a cheering section.

639
00:48:34,027 --> 00:48:38,384
There's something to be
said for accountability.

640
00:48:38,385 --> 00:48:41,956
Are you saying that you
counted on me being here?

641
00:48:41,957 --> 00:48:45,725
No I a-ccounted for
you being here.

642
00:48:45,726 --> 00:48:49,564
Because after I recite this
little number I wrote for you

643
00:48:49,565 --> 00:48:51,900
