He gaffled some meat.

675
00:52:07,602 --> 00:52:12,363
- Jimmy's an idiot.
- Yeah.

676
00:52:15,076 --> 00:52:17,903
Clean that up!

677
00:52:22,183 --> 00:52:27,981
Jimmy? What happened to you?

678
00:52:28,991 --> 00:52:31,092
Prison has been known
to change a man.

679
00:52:31,093 --> 00:52:33,696
I heard you were in a
holding cell for two hours.

680
00:52:33,697 --> 00:52:36,416
I did a lot of thinking
when I was serving time.

681
00:52:36,417 --> 00:52:39,102
Gwen, you are the best
thing to ever happen to me

682
00:52:39,103 --> 00:52:41,903
but I wanted to
run the streets.

683
00:52:41,904 --> 00:52:44,505
But all I ended up doing
was running the streets.

684
00:52:44,506 --> 00:52:49,245
What makes you think I want anything
to do with a washed up ex-con?

685
00:52:49,246 --> 00:52:52,180
You think a dye job
and a wardrobe change

686
00:52:52,181 --> 00:52:56,186
