the times you wronged me?

687
00:52:56,187 --> 00:53:00,788
Wait, Gwen. Please.
Just give me a chance.

688
00:53:01,524 --> 00:53:04,161
- Are you really gonna treat me right?
- Yeah.

689
00:53:04,162 --> 00:53:07,529
And I'm your girlfriend.
Not your bitch.

690
00:53:07,530 --> 00:53:11,101
Maybe just around the boys, you know,
so they don't think I went soft.

691
00:53:11,102 --> 00:53:13,969
Let's get one thing straight
here, Hamburglar.

692
00:53:13,970 --> 00:53:17,339
You're the one standing here
begging me to take you back.

693
00:53:17,340 --> 00:53:22,876
Wait a minute. What are you saying?
Now that makes me your...?

694
00:53:25,616 --> 00:53:28,250
Most def.

695
00:53:48,807 --> 00:53:50,841
- Oh my god.
- You are so funny.

696
00:53:50,842 --> 00:53:54,380
If that guy weren't my boss, I'd
throw him down aflight of stairs.

697
00:53:54,381 --> 00:53:57,851
- Where should we go?
- Yo, Gwen!

698
00:53:57,852 --> 00:54:00,737
- Jimmy? This is...
- Stephen.

699
00:54:00,738 --> 00:54:03,554
But it's spelled
with a P-H.

700
00:54:03,555 --> 00:54:06,859
There are people who still
mispronounce it and call me Stefan.

701
00:54:06,860 --> 00:54:09,328
So I just tell everyone
to call me Steve.

702
00:54:09,329 --> 00:54:11,552
It lessens the
complication.

703
00:54:12,597 --> 00:54:19,203
